    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="90"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <head>90. National Security Decision Memorandum 328<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d90fn1">
                        <p>
                            <seg type="summary">Summary: The President approved a proposal to modify
                                the U.S. commitment of fleet ballistic missile warheads to <gloss
                                    target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>.</seg>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <seg type="source">Source: Ford Library, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                                    >NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box 65, <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSDM_1">NSDM</gloss> 328—Modification of SSBN
                                Commitments to <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>. Top Secret.
                                Copies were sent to the Chairman of the <gloss target="#t_JCS_1"
                                    >JCS</gloss> and the <gloss target="#t_DCI_1">DCI</gloss>.</seg>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1976-05-04">May 4, 1976</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Modification of SSBN Commitments to <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has approved the proposal to modify the U.S. commitment of fleet
                    ballistic missile warheads to <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>. This
                    modification should provide improved survivability of the forces committed to
                    the <pb facs="0389" n="347" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_347"/> General Strike Plan
                        (<gloss target="#t_GSP_1">GSP</gloss>) and allow for some reduction in
                    tactical aircraft requirements for targeting against fixed targets in the <gloss
                        target="#t_GSP_1">GSP</gloss>, thus making such aircraft fully available for
                    other theater operations. Specifically, the U.S. will offer to:</p>
                <p>—Provide <gloss target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss> with the military authority
                    for target assignment, alerting, and missile release for 230 Poseidon RVs from
                    normally alert Poseidon SSBNs and 170 Poseidon RVs from normally non-alert
                    Poseidon SSBNs, vice the current arrangement whereby <gloss target="#t_SACEUR_1"
                        >SACEUR</gloss> is provided the same authority for 150 Poseidon RVs from
                    alert Poseidon SSBNs. In the case of the RVs from normally non-alert SSBNs, it
                    is understood that <gloss target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss>’s missile alerting
                    and release authority becomes operative after the SSBNs have been directed to
                    generate by proper authorities. It is also understood that the Director of
                    Strategic Target Planning will perform the detailed targeting function for these
                    RVs based on a list of <gloss target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss>-designated
                    targets in coordination with <gloss target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss>.</p>
                <p>—Carry the 400 <gloss target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss>-assigned RVs in <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>-pure missiles aboard any number of normally
                    alert or normally non-alert SSBNs, as appropriate, whether located in <gloss
                        target="#t_CINCLANT_1">CINCLANT</gloss>’s or <gloss target="#t_USCINCEUR_1"
                        >USCINCEUR</gloss>’s area of responsibility.</p>
                <p>Any proposal for commitment of additional RVs beyond those specified above shall
                    be submitted to the President for his approval.</p>
                <p>It is to be understood that these commitments to <gloss target="#t_NATO_1"
                        >NATO</gloss> in no way infringe upon the current authority of the President
                    of the United States with regard to missile release either in the <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss> context or as a unilateral national action.
                    The currently approved nuclear weapons safety rules for the Poseidon weapon
                    system will remain in effect for those missiles assigned to <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>. The appropriate authorities aboard SSBNs
                    which carry <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>-assigned missiles will be
                    provided with the necessary command, control and communications documentation
                    required for alerting and launch of missiles in accordance with <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss> authorization procedures.</p>
                <p>The Secretaries of State and Defense, or their designated representatives, may
                    proceed with any necessary consultation and planning in <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss> in accordance with the above.</p>
                <p>This <gloss target="#t_NSDM_1">NSDM</gloss> supersedes relevant portions of
                        <gloss target="#t_NSDM_1">NSDM</gloss> 132 of September 13, 1971.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_SB_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SB_1">Brent Scowcroft</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
